  "version": "0.1.202310121",
  "description": [
    "Checks for rudeimentary collision between 3d objects.",
    "",
    "This collision check is rudimentary for mostly upright objects.",
    "- Perfect for checking collision with 3dBoxes used for floors, walls, bridges, and upright obstacles like characters, furniture, pillars, etc.",
    "- To get the the MODEL collision correct, the Origin needs to be set on bottom middle.",
    "- Or use an invisible 3D Box as a collision mask for the model, just like done sometimes with 2d sprites.",
    "- The collision works properly only on Objects rotated only on Z-axis, since the collision box of the object does not rotate around X-/Y-axis.",
    ""
